 With schools set to return to 'normal', parents and pupils in Cape Town have some concerns. eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - With schools set to return to 'normal', parents and pupils in Cape Town have some concerns. Schools are returning to a full-time schedule from Monday. READ: Back to school | Full-time classes resume The Western Cape Education MEC has welcomed the decision, saying schools in the province are ready. "A large number of our schools haven’t been able to go back, particularly schools in poorer communities where they haven’t had enough space, they haven’t had enough teachers and not that many online facilities, so I’m really pleased," said Debbie Schafer. READ: New conditions for schools as pupils return to class "We’ve seen a lot of learning losses over the last while, and it’s really important for our children to get back to school. So yes, we are ready, we’re as ready as we can be to welcome 1.1 million learners in full every day." * eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports.